<TITLE> Butcher kills Indian 8-year-old over half a dollar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PATNA, India, June 5 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A butcher in eastern India allegedly killed the 8-year-old son of a customer, who owed him 20 rupees or half a dollar, police said on Tuesday. The butcher, whose name was given by police as Bhuvan Rai, pushed the boy into a well after the child's father failed to pay for meat bought last month, Superintendent of Police Kunwar Singh said. Rai was arrested on Monday in Saharsa district in northeastern Bihar, after local villagers found the boy's body floating in the well. A village council had asked Rai and the boy's father to sort out the squabble over the bill peacefully. The average per capita income in India is 32,000 rupees ($790) a year but many Indians still earn less than a dollar a day. ($1=40.50 rupees
